---
---
<section id="lore" class="py-32 bg-zinc-950 relative">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="mb-20 border-l-4 border-amber-600 pl-8">
            <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-6 tracking-tight font-serif">A Village Alive.</h2>
            <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xl max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
                Ashbend isn't a script—it's a living ecosystem powered by a deterministic state engine. NPCs aren't chat endpoints; they have needs, daily schedules, and deeply guarded secrets.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
            <!-- Arin -->
            <div class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-sm bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 p-8 hover:border-amber-500/50 transition-colors h-full">
                <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-4 opacity-10 font-serif text-6xl font-black text-white">A</div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-1 font-serif">Arin</h3>
                <p class="text-amber-500 text-sm font-bold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">The Blacksmith</p>
                <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    Proud and suspicious, but secretly kind. Insult him, and your trust drops. Prove yourself, and he'll remember it when you need a weapon forged.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Mira -->
            <div class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-sm bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 p-8 hover:border-amber-500/50 transition-colors h-full">
                <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-4 opacity-10 font-serif text-6xl font-black text-white">M</div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-1 font-serif">Mira</h3>
                <p class="text-amber-500 text-sm font-bold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">The Innkeeper</p>
                <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    Warm, observant, and deeply gossipy. Tell her a secret, and watch it propagate through the village's relationship graph by dusk.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Tovan -->
            <div class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-sm bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 p-8 hover:border-amber-500/50 transition-colors h-full">
                <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-4 opacity-10 font-serif text-6xl font-black text-white">T</div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-1 font-serif">Tovan</h3>
                <p class="text-amber-500 text-sm font-bold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">The Guard</p>
                <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    Rigid and fearful. As rumors of the demon scout spread, his fear drives him to confront other villagers—sometimes dangerously.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Lysa -->
            <div class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-sm bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 p-8 hover:border-amber-500/50 transition-colors h-full">
                <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-4 opacity-10 font-serif text-6xl font-black text-white">L</div>
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-1 font-serif">Lysa</h3>
                <p class="text-amber-500 text-sm font-bold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">The Mage</p>
                <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    Secretive and morally ambiguous. She holds the key to the shadow looming over the village, but gaining her trust requires careful negotiation.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Gameplay Loop Visual -->
        <div class="mt-12 relative overflow-hidden rounded-sm border border-zinc-800 bg-black">
            <img src="/assets/dawn_after_tasks.jpg" alt="Dawn in Ashbend" class="w-full h-[400px] object-cover opacity-40 mix-blend-luminosity" />
            <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-zinc-950 to-transparent"></div>
            <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 p-10 max-w-2xl">
                <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4 font-serif">The Engine Validates Reality</h3>
                <p class="text-zinc-300 text-lg">
                    LLMs propose actions, but the game engine is the Game Master. If an AI proposes to give you a sword they don't own, the engine rejects it. Everything—from items to trust—is strict, deterministic game data.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
